+# Codex Writer Findings — CartView
+Chain: cartview-260418-195456-dba4
+
+## Findings
+1. [P1] Cancelled orders with stage `internal_code === 'cancelled'` still leak into active totals and buckets — `pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx:425-447` keeps the old inline cancellation filter and only excludes `stageInfo?.internal_code === 'cancel'` or raw `o.status === 'cancelled'`. That misses the past-tense stage code that `getSafeStatus()` already recognizes at `pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx:321-322`, so cancelled orders can remain in `todayMyOrders`, inflate header aggregates, and be bucketed as active orders. FIX: introduce the shared `isCancelledOrder(o)` helper before `todayMyOrders`, include both `cancel` and `cancelled`, and replace the second inline `.filter()` with `.filter(o => !isCancelledOrder(o))`.
+2. [P1] Fix 1 header attribution and rendered-data aggregates are not implemented — `pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx:525-531` still computes `submittedTableTotal` from a status whitelist, and `pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx:788-805` still renders the old `Заказано на стол: X ₸` string in the table tab while the my-tab branch shows only `N блюд · X ₸` without the required `Вы:` prefix. R2 requires `Вы: X блюд · X ₸` and `Стол: X гостя · X блюд · X ₸`, with the amount derived from the orders/items actually rendered in the drawer rather than from `submittedTableTotal`. FIX: remove `submittedTableTotal`, add rendered-data memos for table guest count, dish count, and total across the displayed guests, and update the header copy to the explicit `Вы:` / `Стол:` variants.
+3. [P1] Submitted orders are still folded into `В работе` instead of a dedicated `⏳ Ожидает` bucket — `pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx:456-467` defines only `served` and `in_progress`, so orders with raw status `submitted` and no resolved stage code fall through into `groups.in_progress`. The renderer then hard-codes `bucketOrder = ['served', 'in_progress']` and `bucketDisplayNames` only for those two keys at `pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx:574-577` and `pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx:1005-1024`, which means Fix 2's `pending_unconfirmed` bucket, amber title styling, and ordered placement below `В работе` are all still missing. FIX: expand `statusBuckets` with `pending_unconfirmed`, route raw `submitted` orders there, add the new display name, and update the empty-state `isV8` / `bucketOrder` logic to `['served', 'in_progress', 'pending_unconfirmed']`.
+4. [P1] Table-tab rows still do not surface the `⏳ Ожидает` per-item badge for submitted orders — inside `pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx:880-898`, each order row only renders `getSafeStatus(getOrderStatus(order))`, which collapses pending pre-acceptance rows into the generic `В работе` presentation. Fix 2 explicitly requires the amber `⏳ Ожидает` badge in `Стол` while keeping `Мои` badge-free, but the current row renderer never computes `rawOrderStatus === 'submitted'` and never appends the pending badge in either the zero-item or itemized branches. FIX: compute `stageInfo`, `rawOrderStatus`, and `isOrderPending` inside `guestOrders.map(...)`, then append `⏳ {tr('cart.order.pending_badge', 'Ожидает')}` only in the table-tab row text when `isOrderPending` is true.
+5. [P1] The `Стол` tab still excludes the current guest entirely, so the self-first block from Fix 4 is absent — `pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx:510-512` deliberately removes `myGuestId` from `otherGuestIdsFromOrders`, and the only table-tab card at `pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx:833-916` renders `otherGuestIdsFromOrders.map(...)` with no self block inserted before `SECTION 5`. As a result, `Вы (Гость N)` never appears first in `Стол`, own active orders are invisible there, and own submitted orders also cannot show the required pending badge in that section. FIX: insert a dedicated self card before `SECTION 5`, source it from `ordersByGuestId.get(myGuestId)`, filter it through `!isCancelledOrder(o)`, hide it when the resulting `selfTotal` is zero, and keep the existing other-guests card unchanged below it.
+
+## Summary
+Total: 5 findings (0 P0, 5 P1, 0 P2, 0 P3)
+
+## Prompt Clarity (MANDATORY — do NOT skip this section)
+- Overall clarity: 2
+- Ambiguous Fix descriptions (list Fix # and what was unclear): Fix 1 clearly names the desired header strings, but "rendered-data aggregates" still leaves one implementation detail open: whether the my-tab amount should continue to include cart rows or only persisted orders. Fix 4 names the self-first card behavior clearly, but the prompt mixes behavioral requirements with exact insertion anchors, so it is not obvious which parts are normative versus illustrative.
